Flushing Meadow Park (Queens): At the north end of the park, near the mouth of the Flushing River. View 2 shows W.P.A. workmen cutting pampas grass at 114th Street and 38th Avenue, and view 3 the north end of the park being improved for the 1939-40 World's Fair.

P. L. Sperr

114th Street, north from 38th Avenue. The area on the right will later become part of the New York World's Fair Grounds of 1939-40.

P. L. Sperr

May 20, 1936

114th Street, south from 38th Avenue. The elevated structure is on Roosevelt Avenue and carries the B.M.T. and I.R.T. subway trains. The area on the left is being prepared for the 1939-40 World's Fair.

May 30, 1936

P.L. Sperr
